    <body>
        <h1 class="no-menu">
            Staffing Your DevOps Organization: Agile Development and
            the Division of Labor
        </h1>

        <details>
            <summary class="sum2">
                The extreme division of labor prevailing during much of
                the 20th century was a temporary phenomenon.
            </summary>
        </details>

        <details>
            <summary class="sum2">
                DevOps patterns and practices represent a
                different way of working, and that is based
                on the different demands of the 21<sup>st</sup>
                century.
            </summary>

            <ul>
                <li>
                    DevOps represents a reincarnation of "craft work."
                </li>
            </ul>

        </details>

        <details>
            <summary class="sum2">
                What is the role of the "DevOps toolchain" in establishing this
                new way of working??
            </summary>

            <ul>
                <li>
                    The mechanical, repetitive tasks the assembly-line worker
                    performed in the 20th century must be automated!
                </li>
            </ul>

        </details>

        <details>
            <summary class="sum2">
                How can an enterprise balance the need for highly capable
                specialists with the DevOps demand to "break down silos"?
            </summary>

            <ul>
                <li>
                    An agile enterprise needs to hire people with broad 
                    understanding of various technologies and how they fit into 
                    the enterprise and forward its goals.
                </li>
                <li>
                    Nevertheless, we still are coping with extremely complex
                    technologies, and we will need people who understand them
                    in great depth!
                </li>
            </ul>

        </details>

        <details>
            <summary class="sum2">
                There is no "one size fits all" approach to leading
                a DevOps change.
            </summary>
        </details>

    </body>
</html>
